    "notes": "tl;dr \nI followed this guide for Ubuntu:\nhttps://github.com/lutris/lutris/wiki/How-to:-DXVK\n\ninstalling vulkan drivers was what  got the game to launch for me.\nsudo dpkg --add-architecture i386\nsudo apt install libvulkan1 libvulkan1:i386 \nsudo apt install mesa-vulkan-drivers mesa-vulkan-drivers:i386\n\nBest to google how to do this for your distro.\n\n\nFrom other reports it seems getting this running on AMD through Steam Proton does not work. So I tried Lutris and eventually got the game running (remember to uncheck automatic updates in Lutris or the install will fail). In the process Lutris told me that no vulkan drivers were found and I had to install them. So I did and the game ran. Out of curiosity I tried the game through Steam again and boom, it actually started when before I could not get it to launch at all.",
